00:23:25,246 --> 00:23:28,833
He's talking right to you
in the comfort of your living room.

507
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,085
Well, if I could have watched a preacher

508
00:23:31,252 --> 00:23:34,338
on TV in my own home telling me about God,

509
00:23:34,505 --> 00:23:36,382
that would've made such a difference.

510
00:23:36,465 --> 00:23:38,384
JIM: Mm. Amen.

511
00:23:38,968 --> 00:23:42,680
Especially from someone
who preaches as good as you do, Jim.

512
00:23:43,389 --> 00:23:45,558
- (JIM CHUCKLING)
- (INHALES DEEPLY)

513
00:23:45,641 --> 00:23:47,268
- You think?
- Oh, yeah.

514
00:23:47,435 --> 00:23:49,478
...blow your home over?

515
00:23:50,062 --> 00:23:51,480
You know, we could do that.

516
00:23:53,149 --> 00:23:56,485
You're so much more handsome than he is.

517
00:23:57,737 --> 00:23:58,779
Keep calling.

518
00:23:58,988 --> 00:24:00,198
JIM: Gotta do my homework, baby.

519
00:24:00,281 --> 00:24:01,365
The numbers are on your screen.

520
00:24:01,449 --> 00:24:02,783
Mm. Stop it.

521
00:24:02,950 --> 00:24:04,744
You're distracting me.

522
00:24:04,911 --> 00:24:07,413
...voices of angels.
I hope you enjoy them,

523
00:24:07,496 --> 00:24:08,706
and we have a variety...

524
00:24:09,498 --> 00:24:12,501
Well, we'll have to call the preacher
down in Raleigh

525
00:24:12,668 --> 00:24:14,378
and let him know we got
a better gig down here.

526
00:24:14,545 --> 00:24:16,297
Don't make him cross at you, Jim.

527
00:24:16,464 --> 00:24:18,132
We wanna have him want us back.

528
00:24:18,299 --> 00:24:19,675
JIM: Hold on.

529
00:24:19,842 --> 00:24:21,135
TAMMY: What?

530
00:24:21,302 --> 00:24:22,386
JIM: The car.

531
00:24:23,596 --> 00:24:24,722
I...

532
00:24:26,390 --> 00:24:28,017
I... I parked it here.

533
00:24:28,309 --> 00:24:30,853
Yep, you sure did. Uh-huh.

534
00:24:32,313 --> 00:24:33,439
Well, must've got stolen...

535
00:24:33,606 --> 00:24:34,690
What?

536
00:24:34,774 --> 00:24:36,943
JIM: (GASPS) Oh.

537
00:24:38,027 --> 00:24:39,111
Oh, maybe it got towed.

538
00:24:39,737 --> 00:24:42,615
No, I know I made the payments, so...

539
00:24:44,033 --> 00:24:45,576
I think I made the payments.

540
00:24:45,743 --> 00:24:46,744
Oh, Jim.

541
00:24:46,827 --> 00:24:48,412
Maybe they didn't get
the payments or maybe...

542
00:24:48,496 --> 00:24:49,497
Oh, no.

543
00:24:49,580 --> 00:24:50,873
I don't think I forgot.

544
00:24:51,249 --> 00:24:52,583
- I think I...
- Okay.

545
00:24:52,667 --> 00:24:55,002
- Oh, Tammy, I don't know...
- We need to pray.

546
00:24:55,169 --> 00:24:57,213
Oh, did I? Yes, yes, yes.

547
00:24:57,296 --> 00:24:58,464
TAMMY: Oh, Lord,

548
00:24:58,631 --> 00:25:00,424
we are good soldiers.

549
00:25:00,591 --> 00:25:02,218
- We are here for good.
- Oh, I'm sorry, Tammy.

550
00:25:02,301 --> 00:25:03,970
- We are here for your good.
- I'm so, so, so sorry.

551
00:25:04,053 --> 00:25:05,263
And we ask that you shine your light...

552
00:25:05,346 --> 00:25:06,847
JIM: I shouldn't have put
so much faith in that bank.

553
00:25:06,931 --> 00:25:08,391
God, I'm so sorry.

554
00:25:08,599 --> 00:25:09,725
Jesus, I'm so sorry.

555
00:25:09,892 --> 00:25:11,352
Tammy, I'm sorry.

556
00:25:11,519 --> 00:25:12,979
I'm sorry.

557
00:25:13,145 --> 00:25:14,647
- Jim.
- (SIGHS)

558
00:25:15,690 --> 00:25:16,816
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

559
00:25:16,899 --> 00:25:17,900
MAN: Hey.

560
00:25:18,442 --> 00:25:20,778
Hey, I saw you preach last night.

561
00:25:20,945 --> 00:25:23,864
Those puppets of yours filled me. Deeply.

562
00:25:24,031 --> 00:25:25,324
TAMMY: Oh, thank you.
(CHUCKLING)

563
00:25:25,408 --> 00:25:26,450
JIM: Thank you.

564
00:25:26,617 --> 00:25:28,077
I'm staying in the room next door.

565
00:25:28,577 --> 00:25:30,746
- Can I help you with that?
- (CHUCKLES) No!

566
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:32,540
Well, that's very kind of you...

567
00:25:32,623 --> 00:25:33,624
(BOTH CHUCKLE DRYLY)

568
00:25:33,708 --> 00:25:36,127
...but we don't rightly know
where we're carrying it to.

569
00:25:36,961 --> 00:25:38,587
I work at a local television station

570
00:25:38,754 --> 00:25:40,923
with a minister by the name
of Mr. Pat Robertson.

571
00:25:43,509 --> 00:25:44,927
(CHUCKLES)

572
00:25:45,011 --> 00:25:46,429
He'd get a kick outta you two.

573
00:25:47,054 --> 00:25:49,015
(UPLIFTING MUSIC PLAYING)

574
00:25:51,517 --> 00:25:54,979
WOMAN 1: Yes, honey,
and that's $25 a pledge.

575
00:25:55,062 --> 00:25:58,441
- (PHONES RINGING)
- WOMAN 2: CBN.

576
00:25:58,524 --> 00:26:00,443
Can I take your pledge?

577
00:26:01,861 --> 00:26:03,779
JIM: Well, I'm trying to focus.

578
00:26:05,531 --> 00:26:07,450
And you're just distracting me.

579
00:26:07,616 --> 00:26:09,910
You make me laugh.
I was happy to find...

580
00:26:11,412 --> 00:26:12,705
(MAN CHUCKLING)

581
00:26:12,788 --> 00:26:14,749
JIM: You're so funny, Graham.

582
00:26:14,915 --> 00:26:16,375
- Jim?
- Hey, honey.

583
00:26:16,459 --> 00:26:18,169
Hi, I got a new outfit for the show.

584
00:26:18,336 --> 00:26:20,129
Oh, yes, I love it.

585
00:26:20,629 --> 00:26:22,381
- (CLICKS TONGUE) Jim.
- JIM: Yeah?

586
00:26:22,548 --> 00:26:23,549
You didn't even look at me.

587
00:26:23,716 --> 00:26:24,717
JIM: Oh.

588
00:26:25,343 --> 00:26:26,761
(CHUCKLING) I'm sorry, Tam.

589
00:26:26,927 --> 00:26:28,095
Have I ever told you

590
00:26:28,179 --> 00:26:31,849
that I am the luckiest man
on the face of this planet?

591
00:26:31,932 --> 00:26:33,684
- (TAMMY GIGGLING)
- Have I ever told you that?

592
00:26:33,768 --> 00:26:35,728
- Not today.
- Not today, no?

593
00:26:35,895 --> 00:26:37,104
I'm going to tell you something, too,

594
00:26:37,188 --> 00:26:38,773
but I'm not gonna tell you right now.

595
00:26:38,939 --> 00:26:39,940
You're gonna have to wait.

596
00:26:40,149 --> 00:26:41,984
- No, no, no! (CHUCKLES)
- Yeah.

597
00:26:42,735 --> 00:26:43,986
You just have to.

598
00:26:44,403 --> 00:26:45,738
And there he is.

599
00:26:46,238 --> 00:26:47,323
Every time I try and talk to him,

600
00:26:47,406 --> 00:26:49,450
he just keeps making excuses
not to see me.

601
00:26:49,617 --> 00:26:53,371
Well, my surprise is gonna
make you feel so much better.

602
00:26:53,954 --> 00:26:55,206
I'll be right back.

603
00:26:55,373 --> 00:26:56,415
No, Jim,

604
00:26:56,582 --> 00:26:57,875
- the show's about to start.
- JIM: Hey, Pat!

605
00:26:57,958 --> 00:27:00,002
PAT: Jim! Hey!
JIM: You got a second?

606
00:27:01,212 --> 00:27:03,339
Have you given more thought
to our show idea?

607
00:27:03,422 --> 00:27:04,423
MAN: All right,
let me get you set up.

608
00:27:04,507 --> 00:27:05,841
PAT: Don't you already
have your hands full

609
00:27:05,925 --> 00:27:07,134
with those puppets?

610
00:27:07,301 --> 00:27:09,553
Biggest earner we got.
You stay focused.

611
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:10,805
JIM: Well, yes, of course,

612
00:27:10,930 --> 00:27:13,474
but you shut down CBN at 10 p.m.

613
00:27:13,682 --> 00:27:15,059
Why not do a late-night show?

614
00:27:15,226 --> 00:27:17,019
Just kind of like Johnny Carson
for Christians?

615
00:27:17,103 --> 00:27:19,313
No, Christians don't stay up that late.

616
00:27:19,397 --> 00:27:20,398
Oh, I do.

617
00:27:20,481 --> 00:27:22,066
- I don't sleep at all.
- PAT: What about Tam?

618
00:27:22,233 --> 00:27:24,026
Well, she's gonna miss you at night.

619
00:27:24,193 --> 00:27:26,112
JIM: Tammy loves the idea.
MAN: Tammy, we're on.

620
00:27:26,278 --> 00:27:29,281
MAN 2: Okay, we're live
in five, four, three.

621
00:27:29,365 --> 00:27:31,367
(PAT AND JIM CONTINUE CHATTERING)

622
00:27:33,411 --> 00:27:34,870
Oh, hello, everybody!

623
00:27:35,037 --> 00:27:37,665
CHILDREN: Hi, Tammy!

624
00:27:37,832 --> 00:27:40,209
Well, Jim is a little bit late today,

625
00:27:40,376 --> 00:27:43,045
so, um, the theme of today's show,

626
00:27:43,212 --> 00:27:44,922
how about we make it
all about the importance

627
00:27:45,005 --> 00:27:47,299
of being places on time, hmm?

628
00:27:47,383 --> 00:27:49,385
- (CHUCKLING) Oh, no! Oh, no!
- (CHILDREN LAUGHING)

629
00:27:49,468 --> 00:27:51,262
- I'm sorry, kids!
- There he is.

630
00:27:51,429 --> 00:27:54,598
I'm sorry, Tammy!
I'm sorry, everybody.

631
00:27:54,807 --> 00:27:57,101
I was just having a little,
fun little chat

632
00:27:57,268 --> 00:27:59,854
with Uncle Pat just behind the barn.

633
00:28:00,020 --> 00:28:02,064
Oh, yeah, and what'd you two
fellas get up to without me?

634
00:28:02,231 --> 00:28:05,151
Oh, well, it's actually
something all you kids...

635
00:28:05,234 --> 00:28:06,235
- Mm-hmm.
- ...are gonna wanna

636
00:28:06,318 --> 00:28:07,736
tell your parents about.

637
00:28:07,903 --> 00:28:12,241
It's a brand-new show just for them

638
00:28:12,408 --> 00:28:15,870
right here on CBN!

639
00:28:15,953 --> 00:28:17,413
- (CHILDREN CHEERING)
- Well, amen!

640
00:28:17,496 --> 00:28:20,458
JIM: And it's gonna be called
The 700 Club.

641
00:28:20,624 --> 00:28:22,209
TAMMY: Now, isn't that happy news?

642
00:28:22,376 --> 00:28:25,171
Hallelujah! Yes! Yes!

643
00:28:25,337 --> 00:28:26,338
- SUSIE: Hi, kids.
- Oh.

644
00:28:26,755 --> 00:28:29,967
- (CHILDREN LAUGHING)
- ALL: Hi, Susie Moppet.

645
00:28:30,134 --> 00:28:32,761
Hi, Jim.
Today's a happy day.

646
00:28:32,928 --> 00:28:34,430
Isn't it, kids?
And you know why, Jim?

647
00:28:34,638 --> 00:28:36,223
(CHUCKLES) Why, Susie?

648
00:28:36,390 --> 00:28:39,393
Well, you're gonna have
a new show, kids.

649
00:28:39,477 --> 00:28:41,103
- JIM: Yes.
- (ALL CHUCKLE)

650
00:28:41,270 --> 00:28:44,732
SUSIE: And Jim is gonna have

651
00:28:44,899 --> 00:28:46,442
a baby.

652
00:28:46,525 --> 00:28:47,735
- (CHILDREN EXCLAIM)
- (JIM CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

653
00:28:47,818 --> 00:28:49,695
Look at Tammy,
she's right behind you.

654
00:28:49,778 --> 00:28:51,614
(APPLAUSE)

655
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:54,909
We're gonna have a baby?

656
00:28:55,743 --> 00:28:58,245
Isn't the world just
full of blessings, Jim?

657
00:28:58,329 --> 00:29:00,289
- (CHUCKLING)
- Huh?

658
00:29:00,372 --> 00:29:02,166
- (PHONE RINGING)
- That's right, folks!

659
00:29:02,249 --> 00:29:03,918
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

660
00:29:05,503 --> 00:29:07,379
We're gonna have a baby!

661
00:29:07,463 --> 00:29:08,797
- (CHILDREN CHEERING)
- Oh-ho-ho!

662
00:29:08,923 --> 00:29:11,884
JIM: It's not a drag to be saved.

663
00:29:12,051 --> 00:29:13,802
It's not a boring thing.

664
00:29:13,969 --> 00:29:16,722
That's religion.
See, you got 'em mixed up.

665
00:29:16,889 --> 00:29:19,225
Religion is boring and dull,

666
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:22,561
- but Jesus is life.
- (APPLAUSE)

667
00:29:22,728 --> 00:29:25,272
Now, my next guest is
a new friend to The 700 Club,

668
00:29:25,439 --> 00:29:29,401
and I can smell his chicken,
yes. (LAUGHING)

669
00:29:29,610 --> 00:29:34,114
The Colonel, Colonel Sanders
in The 700 Club!

670
00:29:34,198 --> 00:29:36,617
- (ROCK 'N' ROLL MUSIC PLAYING)
- (CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

671
00:29:41,330 --> 00:29:45,459
Oh, the crowd appreciates you.
I think they like you.

672
00:29:45,626 --> 00:29:47,336
I think they're wanting
some of that chicken.

673
00:29:47,503 --> 00:29:48,796
JIM: I guess
the housewives of America

674
00:29:48,879 --> 00:29:50,172
are thanking you for fixing dinner...

675
00:29:50,256 --> 00:29:52,007
(PHONE RINGING)

676
00:29:53,467 --> 00:29:54,468
Hello.

677
00:29:54,635 --> 00:29:56,053
TAMMY: Oh, hi, Mom.

678
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:59,390
Do you know what time it is?
Why are you calling so late?

679
00:29:59,598 --> 00:30:02,309
Well, Jim says that I need
to rest for my pregnancy,

680
00:30:02,476 --> 00:30:05,854
but, oh, you know me. I can't rest,

681
00:30:06,021 --> 00:30:08,107
so thought I'd call my mother
to keep me company.

682
00:30:08,274 --> 00:30:10,067
I never got a rest.

683
00:30:10,234 --> 00:30:12,319
Oh, I miss working, though.
You know?

684
00:30:12,486 --> 00:30:15,239
It's so lonesome at home all by myself.

685
00:30:15,406 --> 00:30:17,825
Wow! Oh, wow!

686
00:30:17,992 --> 00:30:19,326
And he barely touches me anymore.

687
00:30:19,410 --> 00:30:21,829
And when he does, it's not enthusiastic.

688
00:30:23,289 --> 00:30:26,750
Well, it's up to the wife
to make herself desirable for her husband.

689
00:30:26,917 --> 00:30:29,378
I do that. Oh, I do.

690
00:30:29,878 --> 00:30:31,922
He's just really busy.

691
00:30:32,089 --> 00:30:33,632
- JIM: Really?
- (LAUGHTER ON TV)

692
00:30:33,799 --> 00:30:35,884
So, are you watching Jim's show?

693
00:30:36,051 --> 00:30:38,137
That new talk show of his is on.

694
00:30:38,304 --> 00:30:39,680
Serving God don't feel like

695
00:30:39,763 --> 00:30:41,599
it should be
a money-making opportunity.

696
00:30:41,765 --> 00:30:42,766
TAMMY: Yeah.

697
00:30:43,559 --> 00:30:45,644
You know,
I wanna do what he's doing.

698
00:30:46,061 --> 00:30:48,647
And I wanna sing
and not in a puppet voice.

699
00:30:48,814 --> 00:30:51,358
And I wanna talk about issues
that affect people's daily lives.

700
00:30:51,525 --> 00:30:53,027
And there's so much
that we don't talk about.

701
00:30:53,193 --> 00:30:54,236
There's so many secrets,

702
00:30:54,403 --> 00:30:57,573
and, you know, everyone says
I'm supposed to be tired,

703
00:30:58,198 --> 00:31:00,159
but I just wanna love people.

704
00:31:00,326 --> 00:31:01,744
You got me out of bed

705
00:31:01,827 --> 00:31:03,454
to talk to me about how you're not tired.

706
00:31:03,621 --> 00:31:05,456
Does that make sense to you?

707
00:31:07,541 --> 00:31:08,542
No.

708
00:31:09,585 --> 00:31:12,755
- Sorry.
- Night night, Tam. Take care.

709
00:31:12,921 --> 00:31:14,840
TAMMY: Good night, Mom.
I love you.

710
00:31:15,007 --> 00:31:16,008
Bye.

711
00:31:16,175 --> 00:31:17,509
Okay, bye-bye.

712
00:31:20,679 --> 00:31:21,680
FRED: Who was it?

713
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,684
RACHEL: That was Tam.

714
00:31:25,768 --> 00:31:26,769
FRED: How is she?

715
00:31:26,852 --> 00:31:28,771
RACHEL: Well, it seems like
she's having some trouble

716
00:31:28,854 --> 00:31:30,356
with the pregnancy.
What'd I miss?

717
00:31:30,439 --> 00:31:31,523
JIM: ...a second childhood.

718
00:31:31,607 --> 00:31:32,858
FRED: I don't know.
The sound was off.

719
00:31:33,025 --> 00:31:34,443
You love kids, don't you?

720
00:31:34,526 --> 00:31:36,153
- You love children.
- COLONEL SANDERS: I do.

721
00:31:36,236 --> 00:31:39,657
I have five grandchildren
and 14 great-grandchildren.

722
00:31:39,823 --> 00:31:41,825
- Wow!
- (APPLAUSE)

723
00:31:42,826 --> 00:31:44,745
I bet they're spoiled.
Do you spoil them?

724
00:31:51,001 --> 00:31:52,002
(SIGHS)

725
00:31:53,003 --> 00:31:55,005
Oh, dear Lord God.

726
00:31:57,633 --> 00:32:01,220
What doors are you gonna
open up for me to walk through?

727
00:32:04,473 --> 00:32:06,600
