732
00:32:29,415 --> 00:32:31,417
- (MUSIC CONTINUES)
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)

733
00:32:36,672 --> 00:32:38,048
Well...

734
00:32:39,425 --> 00:32:41,176
What do you think he pays himself?

735
00:32:41,260 --> 00:32:42,261
Oh. (SIGHS)

736
00:32:44,972 --> 00:32:46,140
I should have worn the other dress.

737
00:32:46,306 --> 00:32:47,891
JIM: You look fine, honey.

738
00:32:49,268 --> 00:32:50,436
Oh.

739
00:32:50,519 --> 00:32:51,520
JIM: There he is.

740
00:32:51,687 --> 00:32:53,856
TAMMY: Dede's wearing a mink.
That's a real mink!

741
00:32:54,022 --> 00:32:55,149
And it's warm outside.

742
00:32:55,315 --> 00:32:57,776
You know, we...
we paid for all this, Tammy.

743
00:32:57,860 --> 00:33:01,071
You and me,
from the swimming pool to the hot tub,

744
00:33:01,739 --> 00:33:03,824
and Dede's dead animal.
We paid for it.

745
00:33:03,991 --> 00:33:06,869
Well, the fruit isn't dropping our way,
that's for sure.

746
00:33:06,952 --> 00:33:09,705
- (POLITE CHUCKLE)
- My little stars!

747
00:33:10,289 --> 00:33:11,749
Hello. Hey, Pat!

748
00:33:11,832 --> 00:33:13,000
- What a beautiful place!
- How are you?

749
00:33:13,083 --> 00:33:15,002
- Oh, thank you, thank you!
- Paradise!

750
00:33:15,210 --> 00:33:18,172
Look at that little baby, too.
Positively a chipmunk.

751
00:33:18,338 --> 00:33:19,465
Thanks.

